.docname {Dashboard: Digital Twin Overview}
.include {docs}

The Dashboard serves as your central hub for real-time monitoring and analytics. By default, it opens to the **List (Table) View**, providing a quick, scannable overview of your spaces.

---

## The Default Table View

The default table displays live data for all monitored rooms within your currently selected building. It is designed to give administrators a comprehensive overview at a glance.

The columns shown depend on the saved configuration for that building. By default, a newly registered building starts with the room name and capacity columns. As an administrator you can add any sensor metric as a column, remove columns you don't need, change their order, and save the layout so it persists across sessions. See [Customizing the Data Table](./building-table.qd) for a complete guide.

---

## 🚦 Occupancy Status Indicators

CrowdVision automatically calculates an occupancy status based on the percentage of the room's capacity that is currently filled.

* 🟢 **Empty** — 0% occupancy.
* 🔵 **Normal** — 1% to 50% occupancy.
* 🟠 **Crowded** — 51% to 95% occupancy.
* 🔴 **Full** — 96% to 100% occupancy.
* 🚨 **Overcrowded** — over 100% occupancy. Requires immediate attention.

---

## Building Selection

If your organization manages multiple buildings or facilities across different domains, you can easily navigate between them.
* Locate the **Model Selection Dropdown** at the top of the Dashboard interface.
* Click to open the list of available buildings you have access to.
* Selecting a new building will instantly refresh the table to display the rooms and live sensor data for that specific location.

---

## Switching Views

While the table is perfect for detailed, row-by-row data, CrowdVision also offers visual analytics.
* At the top of the dashboard, you will find a toggle switch featuring **List** and **Graph** buttons.
* Click the **Graph** button to seamlessly transition from the default table to the visual sensor dashboard.
* To return to the data table at any time, simply click the **List** button.

---

## Fullscreen Mode (Focus Mode)

For control rooms, reception desks, or presentations, the Dashboard includes a built-in **Focus Mode**.
* Click the **Fullscreen** button located on the dashboard interface.
* This will expand the current view (whether Table or Graph) to fill your entire screen, hiding your browser's UI and the application's navigation bars. This provides a clean, distraction-free display that is perfect for dedicated monitoring monitors.
* To exit Focus Mode, simply click the fullscreen toggle again or press the `Esc` key on your keyboard.